4
00:00:17,530 --> 00:00:18,330
I won’t ordain.

5
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,500
Po.

6
00:00:25,870 --> 00:00:27,560
It’s okay.

7
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,430
From now on,

8
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:33,640
I’ll take good care of you, Po.

9
00:00:50,570 --> 00:00:51,700
Did you know,

10
00:00:52,170 --> 00:00:54,360
a peach is far more than a mere fruit.

11
00:00:55,210 --> 00:00:56,680
Across many cultures,

12
00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:59,210
it has long been a symbol of love

13
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,220
and of bonds that reach beyond the surface.

14
00:01:02,390 --> 00:01:04,440
With its soft, rounded form

15
00:01:04,670 --> 00:01:06,510
and its delicate, yielding skin,

16
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:10,420
the peach comes to embody longing

17
00:01:11,350 --> 00:01:13,020
and intimacy.

18
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,450
In Chinese tradition,

19
00:01:15,870 --> 00:01:17,970
it is a sign of a life that endures

20
00:01:18,810 --> 00:01:20,000
and immortality.

21
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:24,050
To offer a peach to another

22
00:01:24,470 --> 00:01:27,730
is to begin something meant to last beyond seasons,

23
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:32,700
woven with a happiness and meaning that never fade away.

24
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:26,970
I don’t know if I’m soft-hearted or strong.

25
00:03:28,170 --> 00:03:29,040
But that day,

26
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:32,270
I had the chance to stand face to face

27
00:03:32,270 --> 00:03:34,600
with the man who hurt me and my mother the most.

28
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,130
Long time no see, Po.

29
00:03:38,370 --> 00:03:39,470
How have you been, son?

30
00:03:47,329 --> 00:03:50,770
For a moment, I thought he would say sorry.

31
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,700
But no.

32
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,130
He’s still the same—

33
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:03,570
who sees me as nothing but a tool—

34
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:06,130
