191
00:23:14,370 --> 00:23:15,530
Which flower do you like the most?

192
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:16,770
Oh.

193
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:19,900
I like roses.

194
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,250
No.

195
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:25,270
Don’t just say that to please me.

196
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:28,320
The reason I bought you roses

197
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,500
is because I wanted to try things out

198
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,070
so I could know

199
00:23:32,540 --> 00:23:33,770
what you really

200
00:23:33,770 --> 00:23:35,180
like.

201
00:23:36,170 --> 00:23:37,770
I’m not just saying it to please you.

202
00:23:38,730 --> 00:23:40,270
I really do like roses.

203
00:24:38,130 --> 00:24:39,700
You’ve watched the video, right?

204
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:43,530
I have.

205
00:24:44,700 --> 00:24:45,670
How was it?

206
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:48,810
Well…

207
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,530
I felt a bit emotional.

208
00:24:52,870 --> 00:24:53,670
Emotional?

209
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:01,270
I knew Peach Lover long before I knew you.

210
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,670
Now that he’s saying goodbye,

211
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,170
of course I’d feel that way.

212
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,900
But I’m right here with you now.

213
00:25:16,530 --> 00:25:17,400
That’s not it.

214
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:22,170
You’re not Peach Lover anymore.

215
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:30,070
Then… who am I?

216
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:37,570
You are—

217
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:42,470
Sasom Woraphatcharakorn,

218
00:25:50,170 --> 00:25:51,670
the man I love.

219
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,690
I’m really glad.

220
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:12,320
that we feel the same way.

221
00:26:15,770 --> 00:26:17,470
I mean it, Po.

222
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,100
What I said in the video,

223
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:25,610
that I’m in love,

224
00:26:27,580 --> 00:26:29,270
in a way I’ve never felt before—

225
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:41,200
it’s because of you.

226
00:26:47,330 --> 00:26:48,730
Be with me, Po.

227
00:26:57,570 --> 00:26:58,370
Hey.

228
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:01,900
Did I say something wrong?

229
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:03,670
Not at all.

230
00:27:05,270 --> 00:27:06,730
I just thought

231
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:10,330
you were going to propose to me.

232
00:27:12,730 --> 00:27:13,730
That’s too much, huh?

233
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:16,240
Not at all.

234
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:17,330
I think

235
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:20,380
it’s quite romantic.

236
00:27:21,370 --> 00:27:23,390
But honestly, I do want that.

237
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:26,200
Marriage.

238
00:27:29,100 --> 00:27:30,470
But not now.

239
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:33,670
I’m okay with that.

240
00:27:35,470 --> 00:27:37,600
I’m not expecting anything more.

241
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:39,970
Go ahead. Expect it.

242
00:27:40,870 --> 00:27:41,670
You can.

243
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:45,770
Because I won’t disappoint you.

244
00:27:48,670 --> 00:27:49,470
Thank you.

245
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:53,450
And—

246
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:55,970
what’s your answer?

247
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:04,700
Yeah.

248
00:28:05,530 --> 00:28:07,200
From today… I’m yours.

249
00:28:32,130 --> 00:28:34,400
Why haven’t we been intimate lately?

250
00:28:35,870 --> 00:28:37,940
Well…

251
00:28:38,260 --> 00:28:39,350
I’m scared.

252
00:28:41,170 --> 00:28:43,530
Ever since that happened,

253
00:28:43,530 --> 00:28:44,660
I’m scared that you—

254
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:45,530
But I want to.

255
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:51,930
I want to always be yours.

256
00:28:53,330 --> 00:28:54,130
Sasom.

257
00:28:55,970 --> 00:28:56,900
Really?

258
00:28:57,870 --> 00:28:58,700
Of course.

259
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:00,770
Why would I lie?

260
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,650
Then—

261
00:29:06,430 --> 00:29:08,510
Guess the party’s ending early then.

262
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,100
What are you doing?

263
00:30:25,470 --> 00:30:26,530
Come here.

264
00:30:27,270 --> 00:30:28,070
Hurry.

265
00:30:38,330 --> 00:30:39,730
I’m gonna film this,

266
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:43,950
to keep it as a memory for us.

267
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:47,140
Let’s film this together.

268
00:31:07,370 --> 00:31:10,530
Looking back to the day I signed up for Peach Lover,

269
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:14,040
I never thought

270
00:31:15,350 --> 00:31:16,860
I’d end up here.

271
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:22,140
From an ordinary freelancer drifting through life,

272
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:26,300
from a fan watching him from afar,

273
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:28,330
today,

274
00:31:29,310 --> 00:31:31,220
I’ve become the one he chose

275
00:31:31,410 --> 00:31:32,730
to stay by his side.

276
00:31:35,170 --> 00:31:37,230
Throughout this journey,

277
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:39,540
it was never easy.

278
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,850
There were smiles,

279
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,220
tears,

280
00:31:44,740 --> 00:31:46,020
pain,

281
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:49,140
and fear.

282
00:31:51,550 --> 00:31:52,840
But every time I turned around,

283
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,670
I saw him right here.

284
00:32:00,530 --> 00:32:01,530
He is Sasom,

285
00:32:02,870 --> 00:32:05,570
the only man who never let me fight alone.

286
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:13,050
To me,

287
00:32:14,690 --> 00:32:16,820
love is like painting,

288
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:20,900
starting from a sketch that isn’t clear yet,

289
00:32:22,450 --> 00:32:25,330
gradually adding color until it becomes complete,

290
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:27,870
and every color

291
00:32:28,810 --> 00:32:30,450
brings this picture to life,

292
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:33,500
and that is you.

293
00:32:39,670 --> 00:32:41,060
Who would’ve thought?

294
00:32:41,810 --> 00:32:43,530
that a new peach

295
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,620
would find true love,

296
00:32:47,210 --> 00:32:49,220
not from filming videos,

297
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,580
or competition,

298
00:32:51,810 --> 00:32:52,670
or sex,

299
00:32:55,670 --> 00:32:57,440
but a real love,

300
00:32:58,850 --> 00:33:00,950
that we choose to keep,

301
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:05,290
with both our hearts.

302
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:15,130
This may not be the most complete ending,

303
00:33:21,330 --> 00:33:23,600
this may not be the most perfect ending,

304
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:27,620
but it will be the beginning

305
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:31,890
of the most beautiful part for me and him.

306
00:33:35,970 --> 00:33:37,670
And I promise that

307
00:33:39,670 --> 00:33:41,400
from now on, no matter what happens,

308
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:46,640
I will keep every second

309
00:33:49,220 --> 00:33:51,890
as a memory that will never fade.

310
00:35:22,270 --> 00:35:23,530
You sleep like a kitten.

311
00:35:37,470 --> 00:35:38,490
Is something wrong?

312
00:35:39,150 --> 00:35:40,540
Why are you up so early?

313
00:35:43,770 --> 00:35:44,280
Here you go.

314
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:46,720
I made this for you.

315
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:49,740
I figured you must’ve been tired from last night.

316
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:59,070
Careful, it’s hot.

317
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:13,870
Did you add milk?

318
00:36:14,130 --> 00:36:15,170
Why does it smell better?

319
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:18,100
I added a bit of honey.

320
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,700
I’m just worried my boyfriend

321
00:36:21,220 --> 00:36:23,220
might get sick on New Year’s.

322
00:36:39,470 --> 00:36:40,610
It’s the New Year.

323
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:42,380
Don’t look all messy.

324
00:36:42,990 --> 00:36:43,750
Got it?

325
00:36:44,330 --> 00:36:45,700
Stop teasing me.

326
00:36:50,330 --> 00:36:51,860
I’m not teasing.

327
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:56,290
I just like your face when you wake up,

328
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:57,860
very much.

329
00:36:59,700 --> 00:37:01,570
Why are you being so sweet today?

330
00:37:02,970 --> 00:37:03,470
Well,

331
00:37:04,170 --> 00:37:06,300
it’s New Year’s.

332
00:37:07,170 --> 00:37:08,610
So I want

333
00:37:08,850 --> 00:37:12,500
this morning to be the best one for us.

334
00:37:19,900 --> 00:37:21,070
Then—

335
00:37:22,750 --> 00:37:25,110
let me stay like this a little longer, okay?

336
00:37:27,270 --> 00:37:28,500
Stay like this all day.

337
00:38:13,270 --> 00:38:14,700
Are you drawing me?

338
00:38:26,100 --> 00:38:28,130
That definitely looks like me.

339
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:41,530
Hey.

340
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:44,200
Don’t come too close.

341
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,570
I won’t get it right.

342
00:38:46,730 --> 00:38:48,130
You didn’t answer me.

343
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:19,200
Why are you looking at me like that?

344
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:25,830
Do you know,

345
00:39:26,950 --> 00:39:29,200
when you’re focused like this,

346
00:39:30,370 --> 00:39:32,030
you’re so damn kissable.

347
00:39:52,270 --> 00:39:53,670
You’ve fallen for me, I can tell.

348
00:40:16,730 --> 00:40:18,570
You’ve drawn a lot of me, Po.

349
00:40:24,670 --> 00:40:26,240
But my favorite

350
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:27,600
is you.

351
00:41:37,670 --> 00:41:40,000
Today, I want to tell our story

352
00:41:40,610 --> 00:41:42,290
to the people we love,

353
00:41:42,750 --> 00:41:45,700
how we got here.

354
00:41:58,300 --> 00:41:59,470
I’ll help tell it.

355
00:42:02,730 --> 00:42:06,130
When we first met, I was so excited.

356
00:42:10,070 --> 00:42:12,300
He really looked like a celebrity.

357
00:42:24,570 --> 00:42:26,430
But he’s nothing like he is on screen.

358
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:28,740
On screen, he looks cool,

359
00:42:29,060 --> 00:42:32,990
but in real life, he’s really flirty.

360
00:42:35,170 --> 00:42:37,200
Yeah, a little. Just a little.

361
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,570
That day, I saw him as a kitten,

362
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:45,000
a little kitten lost in a big city.

363
00:42:46,670 --> 00:42:47,600
So I

364
00:42:48,490 --> 00:42:50,410
just wanted to take care of him.

365
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,520
At first, I was scared.

366
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:01,180
Because every time he smiled,

367
00:43:01,740 --> 00:43:03,710
I couldn’t catch my breath.

368
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:17,100
But once we were really together,

369
00:43:18,900 --> 00:43:20,400
he wasn’t as tough as I thought,

370
00:43:21,930 --> 00:43:24,130
he was just trying to look strong for everyone.

371
00:43:33,900 --> 00:43:35,820
When we first got close,

372
00:43:38,020 --> 00:43:41,280
I liked sitting there, listening to him draw.

373
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:46,760
I liked watching him when he focused on his work.

374
00:43:54,730 --> 00:43:57,670
I liked how his ears turned red when he got shy.

375
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:08,450
And here you are, talking only about the good parts.

376
00:44:08,450 --> 00:44:10,580
You’re not mentioning when we fought,

377
00:44:10,580 --> 00:44:11,080
cried,

378
00:44:11,870 --> 00:44:14,200
or walked away from each other.

379
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:16,650
I won’t.

380
00:44:17,540 --> 00:44:18,910
Because in the end,

381
00:44:19,190 --> 00:44:20,850
we always found our way back.

382
00:44:22,590 --> 00:44:24,210
And that’s what matters most.

383
00:44:35,570 --> 00:44:36,600
We’ve been through problems,

384
00:44:37,530 --> 00:44:38,330
through family,

385
00:44:39,730 --> 00:44:41,500
through so much together.

386
00:44:43,770 --> 00:44:45,870
Some days, it felt like the world was falling apart on us.

387
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:49,530
Po.

388
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:14,730
But he never left me.

389
00:45:16,470 --> 00:45:17,870
No matter how stressed he was,

390
00:45:19,300 --> 00:45:21,370
no matter what the past brought back,

391
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:24,730
he was still here every day.

392
00:45:28,930 --> 00:45:32,330
I want to be that place for him too.

393
00:45:38,700 --> 00:45:39,470
Hey.

394
00:45:40,220 --> 00:45:41,700
What you just said—

395
00:45:43,150 --> 00:45:44,610
I’m about to cry.

396
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:56,950
On the day I

397
00:45:57,940 --> 00:46:01,050
decided to take his hand on camera,

398
00:46:05,100 --> 00:46:07,200
I wasn’t trying to start anything over,

399
00:46:13,930 --> 00:46:16,100
I just wanted his ordinary life

400
00:46:18,100 --> 00:46:19,570
to not have to be hidden anymore.

401
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:29,240
I wanted everyone to know

402
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:34,030
that this person is the most important to me.

403
00:46:47,600 --> 00:46:48,910
The two of us

404
00:46:49,480 --> 00:46:51,500
aren’t perfect.

405
00:46:52,860 --> 00:46:55,870
We fight, we get upset,

406
00:46:55,870 --> 00:46:57,560
and argue over silly things.

407
00:46:58,780 --> 00:47:00,000
But in the end,

408
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:05,090
we choose to come back to each other.

409
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,800
He is my home.

410
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:13,950
And I’ll be his home too.

411
00:47:17,610 --> 00:47:18,970
I love him so much.

412
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:21,960
And from now on,

413
00:47:22,990 --> 00:47:24,630
I want him

414
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:27,610
to be in every frame of my life.

415
00:47:41,130 --> 00:47:42,330
I feel the same.
